cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CR. 

The paper deals with a computer vision task of person search, which involves object detection, feature extraction, and identity recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel center loss to improve feature representations, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. The paper also evaluates its proposed model on two benchmarks, indicating a focus on performance evaluation, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category. Finally, the paper addresses the challenge of unavailable bounding boxes and occlusions, indicating a possible focus on security and privacy, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a less likely but still possible category.
